Listing 7-12 shows that the RetroBoardRepository interface includes the following:
•	
ReactiveMongoRepository: This is a Mongo-specific 
interface with reactive support. It extends from the 
ReactiveCrudRepository, ReactiveSortingRepository, and 
ReactiveQueryByExampleExecutor interfaces. It brings all the usual 
methods (insert, save, find*, etc.) but in this case using the Flux 
and Mono types. Spring Data and Project Reactor will implement 
these interfaces using all the reactive support.
•	
Mono<RetroBoard>: As in previous versions, you can define your own 
find* methods and even use your own queries, in this case using 
the MongoDB query language. We are using the @Query annotation 
to define a particular query that will find a Card by its UUID among 
all the retroBoard objects. Of course, this approach is not the best 
because you can narrow your search if you facilitate the retroBoard 
UUID or do a different map reduce option. The idea here is that you 
can extend, use, and create your own custom queries.
