Notice in the RetroBoardPersistenceCallback class that we are now using the 
ReactiveBeforeConvertCallback interface. This interface has a method, called 
onBeforeConvert, that expects to return a Publisher. This method will be used to add 
a UUID when a RetroBoard entity doesn’t have one. Also note that we are returning a 
Mono, in this case with the Mono.just() method. Again, this is one way to implement this 
business rule, but you can add logic to the service if you prefer. With the code in  
Listing 7-13, we are making our service as clean as possible.
